Reasoning: The paper discusses the computation of semantic similarity and relatedness in geographic information science and semantics, which suggests a focus on natural language processing and information retrieval. This aligns with the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also describes a new dataset for evaluating computational measures of geo-semantic relatedness and similarity, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of geographic information science and semantics suggests a potential overlap with the sub-category of cs.DB (Databases).
